WEBVTT

00:01.506 --> 00:06.833
Welcome to Baria Temple International Church's Podcast.

00:06.853 --> 00:13.342
I am your host Timothy, and we're here together on this beautiful day to hear from God.

00:14.724 --> 00:20.572
So let's all prepare ourselves to receive what God has in store for us today.

00:22.174 --> 00:22.755
Let's begin.

00:24.177 --> 00:30.866
If you haven't noticed, we are building out an identity together as a church.

00:31.266 --> 00:42.602
And each of the sub-series that we have embarked on has taken us one step closer to identifying who we are as Berea Temple International Church.

00:43.863 --> 00:48.670
So far, we have identified that we are an A.G. Church.

00:49.131 --> 00:52.495
We worked through our core foundational doctrines of the Church.

00:52.736 --> 00:55.640
We call these our 16 fundamental truths.

00:57.723 --> 01:00.146
Then we took a cue out of

01:00.258 --> 01:10.072
the book I Am a Church Member by Tom Rayner, and that added to our identity to the fact that we are A.G. Church members.

01:12.135 --> 01:24.051
But today, today we're going to embark on a journey of understanding our role as A.G. Church members in bringing hope and healing to our community.

01:25.093 --> 01:28.818
See, it's all well and good to say that we are something

01:29.026 --> 01:30.369
We are AG.

01:30.469 --> 01:32.253
We are AG church members.

01:32.574 --> 01:33.696
We are Christians.

01:33.797 --> 01:35.320
We are whatever.

01:37.404 --> 01:43.277
It's all well and good to say that we are something, but it's meaningless if we don't put it into action.

01:44.380 --> 01:49.010
It means nothing if we talk the talk, but don't walk the walk.

01:50.050 --> 01:51.993
What does it mean to be Christian?

01:52.013 --> 01:53.855
We talked about this a couple of weeks ago.

01:54.196 --> 01:56.299
It means to be Christ-like.

01:56.319 --> 02:13.543
But if I walk out of here and I'm cussing up a storm at the grocery store and the person who cut me off and I flip them the bird and then I leave there and I go and I get mad and I've got my fifth of whiskey and I go and I pour one back out of the park, does that say that I am a Christian?

02:14.925 --> 02:15.986
Probably not.

02:16.898 --> 02:19.782
Does that reflect the Christ that I serve?

02:20.142 --> 02:21.384
No, of course not.

02:23.647 --> 02:30.196
So saying you're a Christian, I'm sorry for those that think so, means absolutely nothing.

02:34.281 --> 02:41.410
To do, to be, to walk the walk is what matters.

02:43.033 --> 02:44.114
I can say,

02:44.866 --> 02:53.894
I'm the world's greatest IT programmer, and I'm gonna sit down on a computer next to Brother Prince, and that fact is gonna be woefully disproven.

02:56.577 --> 03:04.264
I can say that I am the world's greatest gardener, but next to the Ferris family, I couldn't grow nothing and nothing.

03:08.548 --> 03:10.190
We have to walk the walk.

03:10.450 --> 03:14.674
We have to put feet to the fire, so to speak.

03:17.698 --> 03:22.784
Today as we continue in our theme we are, we're gonna add to our identity.

03:24.366 --> 03:30.232
We're not gonna settle with only being AG church members because that ends with us.

03:30.593 --> 03:33.496
That tells the world, come join us.

03:35.078 --> 03:46.130
If we stop at this side, if we stop our identity here, we're telling the rest of the world, you come here, join us, do what we're doing.

03:48.226 --> 03:49.187
Is that biblical?

03:50.348 --> 03:52.370
Are we good students of God's word?

03:57.995 --> 04:00.398
See this, this ends with us.

04:01.258 --> 04:02.379
This ends with self.

04:03.781 --> 04:06.683
But the Father has not called us to be selfish.

04:07.204 --> 04:09.866
He's called us to be selfless.

04:11.228 --> 04:17.874
He said, go and make disciples and we can't do that sitting here in the pews.

04:20.034 --> 04:23.477
We can't go and fulfill the great commission.

04:23.778 --> 04:29.303
We can't fulfill the great commandment sitting on our bottoms in these red padded pews.

04:31.325 --> 04:33.747
We have to go, say go.

04:33.787 --> 04:42.936
So I've entitled this sub, next sub series that we're going to do.

04:42.976 --> 04:48.882
I have entitled hope and healing for our community.

04:50.178 --> 05:01.979
And so what that's going to do is it's going to add to our identity statement that we are AG church members who offer hope and healing to our community.

05:02.360 --> 05:03.562
That is who we are.

05:03.862 --> 05:05.165
He is Waymaker.

05:05.505 --> 05:10.675
We are those who connect to the Waymaker to our community.

05:11.496 --> 05:12.658
We are the bridge.

05:12.898 --> 05:20.888
We are the hands and feet of Jesus who go out into a lost and dying world and offer hope and healing to our community.

05:21.228 --> 05:29.419
There is a passage that should be fairly well familiar to most of you in Jeremiah chapter 29 and verse 11.

05:29.739 --> 05:32.122
This one should be relatively familiar.

05:32.482 --> 05:35.426
It says, for I know the plans I have for you says the Lord.

05:35.686 --> 05:40.212
They're plans for good and not for disaster to give you a future and a hope.

05:40.232 --> 05:41.874
How many would say amen to that?

05:44.514 --> 05:45.896
But I want you to back up a little bit.

05:47.278 --> 05:51.665
I want you to go just a few verses back in that same chapter, Jeremiah 29.

05:51.906 --> 05:55.451
So if you have your Bibles, this is where we're going to start.

05:55.472 --> 05:56.714
Jeremiah chapter 29.

05:56.754 --> 06:02.102
And I want us to look at a passage that might not be quite so familiar.

06:03.244 --> 06:06.409
Look at verse seven of Jeremiah chapter 29.

06:08.873 --> 06:09.554
Says this.

06:10.082 --> 06:16.760
It says in work for the peace and prosperity of the city where I sent you into exile.

06:17.261 --> 06:23.398
Pray to the Lord for it, for its welfare will determine your welfare.

06:25.283 --> 06:26.386
It's no secret

06:27.298 --> 06:30.121
that our city is in need of a savior.

06:30.141 --> 06:33.945
It's no secret that our citizens' health and welfare are in peril.

06:34.146 --> 06:40.372
And it should be no secret that the only answer for the community, for St. Louis, is Jesus Christ.

06:43.916 --> 06:44.357
Oh man.

06:46.259 --> 06:47.801
Brother, we need to go have our own church.

06:48.041 --> 06:53.687
Come on.

06:53.707 --> 06:56.370
Just take a moment to cycle through the pictures.

06:57.698 --> 06:58.860
These are all St. Louis.

06:59.521 --> 07:04.729
These aren't just stock photos from the internet that I tried to pick to dig at your heart.

07:05.330 --> 07:07.314
These are all St. Louisans.

07:07.554 --> 07:14.085
These are all people that we call friends, neighbors in our city.

07:19.033 --> 07:22.258
And there's only one answer to the gun violence.

07:22.658 --> 07:25.161
There is only one answer to the homelessness.

07:25.461 --> 07:29.625
There is only one answer to the drug epidemic, and that is Jesus.

07:30.906 --> 07:34.710
But how are they gonna have Jesus if we don't go and tell them?

07:37.513 --> 07:42.198
How are they gonna have Jesus if we only sit in the pews on Sunday?

07:43.819 --> 07:45.281
And that's our faith.

07:45.641 --> 07:50.386
That's working out our faith with fear and trembling because I'm afraid of going out there.

07:54.658 --> 07:59.925
And just who are the hands and feet of Jesus in a dying world?

08:00.046 --> 08:00.947
What does scripture say?

08:01.027 --> 08:01.648
Who is that?

08:02.850 --> 08:03.330
Say us.

08:04.953 --> 08:05.974
Come on now, say us.

08:07.536 --> 08:10.701
We are the hands and feet of Jesus.

08:10.981 --> 08:12.924
We are the church.

08:15.207 --> 08:17.330
We, you and me.

08:18.402 --> 08:21.345
I don't care what the Presbyterians are doing down the street.

08:21.766 --> 08:31.457
I don't care what our sister, A.G., church is doing because God is raising up that body for a different purpose, a different plan, a different mission, a different goal.

08:31.717 --> 08:35.622
And frankly, some of those preachers have completely lost their ever-loving minds.

08:38.244 --> 08:39.826
But I know what he's called us to.

08:41.348 --> 08:43.851
He's called us to be the church.

08:44.351 --> 08:46.674
We are the church.

08:47.170 --> 08:52.375
Our passage tells us that the city's welfare will determine our welfare.

08:53.176 --> 08:58.461
If the city is prosperous, we have the opportunity to be prosperous.

08:59.563 --> 09:07.050
So today we're gonna step out on a journey to seek and to save that which is lost.

09:13.737 --> 09:14.738
But it's for one reason.

09:16.706 --> 09:27.459
It's because we are A.G. church members who offer hope and healing to our community through the power of the Holy Spirit.

09:29.682 --> 09:29.983
Amen?

09:34.448 --> 09:35.490
So here's what we're gonna do.

09:36.531 --> 09:42.258
Our sub-series for the next six weeks or so is hope and healing for our community.

09:43.170 --> 09:49.241
Today specifically, if you're a note taker, our title for today's message.

09:50.905 --> 09:52.007
And it's just going to keep rolling.

09:52.027 --> 09:54.632
Guys, if you'll go down to the next slide for me, please manually.

09:57.517 --> 10:00.082
Is God's heart for our city?

10:00.102 --> 10:06.514
The first thing I want us to look at when we talk about offering hope and healing for our city,

10:07.234 --> 10:16.968
is I want us to explore God's heart for our city, for the city of St. Louis, and what our part is in his divine plan.

10:19.973 --> 10:26.442
First thing that we're going to look at is we need to understand God's plan for St. Louis and our role in it.

10:29.527 --> 10:30.448
We've talked a lot.

10:30.488 --> 10:33.152
We hit theology, the fundamental truths.

10:33.693 --> 10:34.354
We hit

10:34.562 --> 10:39.072
who we are in this forest just day-to-day practice inside the building.

10:40.335 --> 10:44.845
But for the next six messages, we're going to get very practical.

10:45.527 --> 10:47.090
Very rubber meets the road.

10:47.266 --> 10:50.552
very down and dirty, nitty-gritty.

10:51.033 --> 10:55.100
This is what we as a church need to be doing.

10:55.381 --> 10:59.829
We need to understand God's plan for St. Louis and our role in it.

11:00.049 --> 11:02.393
Again, we go back to our passage that we had.

11:02.634 --> 11:09.586
Jeremiah 29.7 says, calls us to seek peace and prosperity for our city.

11:10.594 --> 11:18.462
But this command is not just about passive observation, but active involvement in God's plan for our community.

11:18.762 --> 11:20.044
Can I tell you something?

11:20.844 --> 11:23.627
And you're gonna be mad at me when I'm done saying this.

11:26.190 --> 11:36.020
I don't know what else you have going on in your life, but it all comes second to the mission and the purpose that God has created you for as a church.

11:37.882 --> 11:38.322
Listen,

11:39.778 --> 11:42.522
Date night with husband or wife, that's wonderful.

11:43.984 --> 11:52.395
But it doesn't trump if God has called us together unified to an outreach event.

11:54.157 --> 11:57.321
Or a, now I'm not talking about we go to the movies.

11:58.563 --> 12:09.778
I'm talking about God has put a plan and a purpose and we together as a church are making a concerted effort to reach our community and we have

12:10.018 --> 12:21.681
prayer meeting, a outreach event, a go feed the homeless, a go walk the streets, a prayer walk, whatever those things are, whatever else you've got going on.

12:24.267 --> 12:26.371
Church is not a social event.

12:29.016 --> 12:31.922
Church is training camp for the battle

12:32.066 --> 12:34.128
that we are all called to fight in.

12:34.148 --> 12:36.831
We are all soldiers in God's army.

12:36.991 --> 12:48.962
I know we don't like that metaphor, that imagery, because for a lot of us who have military family or other situations, I know some of that draws up yuck feelings.

12:50.824 --> 12:57.391
But when it comes to the kingdom, the Bible says the enemy is like a roaring lion seeking whom he may devour.

12:59.633 --> 13:00.914
Are we as a body

13:01.858 --> 13:04.542
going to rise up at the corner of Russell and Compton.

13:04.782 --> 13:16.059
Are we going to watch the enemy destroy our neighbor across the street and do nothing to intervene?

13:19.745 --> 13:24.072
God has called us to active involvement in his plan.

13:26.035 --> 13:27.817
Now, I'm not saying there aren't issues.

13:27.857 --> 13:30.301
There aren't opportunities that take our attention.

13:30.401 --> 13:30.962
Yes.

13:33.154 --> 13:47.136
But when we're talking about things that are optional, that are part of our discretionary time spending, how do they compare to what God is doing?

13:47.176 --> 13:51.663
And here's another one, parents, that I'm gonna, you're gonna be mad at me and it's okay.

13:51.683 --> 13:52.364
I love you anyway.

13:53.786 --> 14:01.618
Probably one of my biggest pet peeves as a pastor is parents who keep their kids home from Wednesday night youth because, well, it's just youth group, it's not church.

14:02.082 --> 14:03.163
It's not the deep teaching.

14:04.285 --> 14:11.053
But see, that's where they go and they get teaching at their level to understand what God is doing in their lives today.

14:11.634 --> 14:14.978
Well, but they've got homework and homework comes first.

14:16.059 --> 14:16.339
Really?

14:16.359 --> 14:19.083
And I know we can debate over that.

14:19.864 --> 14:21.426
Yes, you need a good job.

14:21.786 --> 14:23.628
Yes, you need a good education.

14:23.989 --> 14:31.538
But we're talking about an hour and a half a week for youth group compared to

14:31.682 --> 14:52.594
All the other hours that they have, Monday night, Tuesday night, the rest of Wednesday night, Thursday night, Friday night, all day Saturday, the rest of Sunday, we're asking for an hour and a half that we allow the people that we've asked to train and to pour into our students so that they hear Christ.

14:54.082 --> 15:03.333
Not in a message that's designed for a general audience, but for a word that is specifically spoken to their age group.

15:03.353 --> 15:06.557
Youth ministry is vital when done right.

15:08.219 --> 15:09.441
It's not club.

15:10.162 --> 15:11.323
It's not play.

15:11.924 --> 15:17.751
Yes, there is a moment of silliness and games to encourage kids to bring friends and things like that.

15:18.051 --> 15:23.538
But it is putting an active faith into the hearts of our students.

15:26.114 --> 15:31.765
We need to understand when we talk about understanding what our role is, is to be active.

15:32.567 --> 15:38.137
We need to understand that God has placed us for a divine purpose.

15:39.019 --> 15:42.225
We need to recognize our divine placement.

15:42.826 --> 15:44.690
Acts 17, verse 26.

15:45.954 --> 15:50.462
says that from one man he created all the nations throughout the whole earth.

15:50.743 --> 15:56.674
He decided beforehand when they should rise and fall and he determined their boundaries.

15:56.734 --> 16:02.124
He decided beforehand when they should rise and fall.

16:03.587 --> 16:07.674
God's placed us in St. Louis for a reason and a purpose.

16:07.694 --> 16:09.778
I might even add, for a season

16:09.826 --> 16:10.547
and a purpose.

16:10.847 --> 16:12.909
Listen, all of us come and go.

16:13.149 --> 16:19.895
We have had friends in the life of being part of Berea Temple that have new friends have come in and then they've had to go out.

16:19.915 --> 16:23.298
Not for any other reason, then life moved them on.

16:23.478 --> 16:24.239
It's okay.

16:24.539 --> 16:26.120
It's completely acceptable.

16:26.380 --> 16:34.688
They have had to move for financial reasons or for job situations or for wedding or funeral or whatever else it may be.

16:35.008 --> 16:39.812
There has been a season that they were part of the body of Christ at Berea Temple.

16:39.792 --> 16:46.861
and God has placed each one of us here for a reason, a season, and a purpose.

16:46.881 --> 16:52.588
Luke chapter 19, and verse 10 says, for the son of man came to seek and save those who were lost.

16:52.648 --> 17:02.341
And then if you go to Esther, chapter four, verse 14 says, if you keep quiet at a time like this, deliverance and relief for the Jews will arise from some other place.

17:02.641 --> 17:04.664
But you and your relatives will die.

17:04.964 --> 17:09.650
Who knows if perhaps you were made queen for such a time as this?

17:09.698 --> 17:17.549
Our presence here in this part of his grand design is for our lives and for his life in the city.

17:19.051 --> 17:32.370
He's placed us here to seek out and to offer salvation through Jesus Christ to those who are lost, those who wander the streets, those that are looking for peace inside the barrel of a syringe.

17:38.882 --> 17:49.378
As we look for God's heart for the city, we need to recognize that our placement in here in St. Louis is part of his own divine plan.

17:51.601 --> 18:02.176
With an average population of 2.2 million people in the St. Louis metropolitan area, God has entrusted us with a significant community.

18:02.357 --> 18:04.981
Remember our passage in 29 verse seven?

18:06.122 --> 18:08.626
Look over the city, pray for it,

18:09.058 --> 18:12.643
Each person here is part of his grand design.

18:12.883 --> 18:16.988
However, our community faces substantial challenges.

18:17.789 --> 18:26.240
Approximately 219,000 individuals in our area struggle with substance use disorders.

18:27.923 --> 18:28.623
219,000.

18:33.490 --> 18:36.754
How many churches of 200 could we start?

18:37.058 --> 18:43.506
If we, as Berea Temple said, we are going to only attack the drug epidemic in our city.

18:45.488 --> 18:51.055
What would the kingdom of Christ and St. Louis look like if we said we are going to reach these people?

18:51.515 --> 18:55.741
Yes, we love everybody else, but we're going to reach this group of people.

18:56.702 --> 19:00.066
And we were going to make a difference in that community.

19:01.888 --> 19:06.834
Average church in America is under 200 people if you wonder where I got the 200 number.

19:11.970 --> 19:25.590
About 140,000 adults have experienced major depressive episodes in the past year, just in the last year.

19:26.671 --> 19:39.730
Not the entirety of all of the city, not in the entirety of keeping statistics across mental health issues, but in the last year, 140,000 people have experienced major depressive episodes.

19:40.290 --> 19:42.815
These numbers aren't just statistics.

19:42.835 --> 19:45.580
These represent real people.

19:47.223 --> 19:49.748
Real people in need of a real God.

19:51.030 --> 19:54.557
Real people in need of real hope and healing.

19:57.722 --> 19:59.666
And we as the church are called.

20:00.290 --> 20:02.733
to provide hope and healing.

20:03.153 --> 20:06.998
We are A.G. We are spirit filled.

20:07.098 --> 20:15.748
We are church members who know who God is and what He is and how He works and how the Holy Spirit moves in and through us.

20:17.310 --> 20:21.194
And we can provide that to a lost and dying world.

20:21.735 --> 20:24.658
But we can't do that if we're caught up in our own stuff.

20:25.154 --> 20:29.300
We can't do that if we're caught up and I want church to be my way.

20:29.480 --> 20:31.343
I want church to be this way.

20:31.363 --> 20:33.206
I want church to do that or this.

20:33.466 --> 20:34.327
It's all about me.

20:34.367 --> 20:35.449
It's not about you.

20:39.294 --> 20:42.519
It's about 144,000 people that need to know Jesus.

20:43.741 --> 20:53.074
It's about 200 and some thousand people who need to stop looking in the barrel of a syringe till they stop looking at the bottom of a spoon.

20:55.170 --> 20:57.493
who need to stop sticking straws in their nose.

21:04.143 --> 21:05.245
Because here's what I can tell you.

21:10.192 --> 21:19.506
If the church would have reached out to my mom and been Jesus to her, my life would have been very much different.

21:22.754 --> 21:30.123
Thankfully the Lord saved me, guided me, called me and set my feet in spite of the church's actions.

21:32.846 --> 21:36.831
Because I can guarantee you there's people sitting in this room today or that are watching online.

21:38.734 --> 21:43.059
You're sitting here today, but you're mad at somebody in the church.

21:45.863 --> 21:51.890
Because they disregarded a loved one, they handled the situation like they shouldn't have.

21:55.746 --> 22:01.211
I have a friend, and I know he's not watching, but on the off chance, his name is Robert.

22:03.333 --> 22:13.143
And I brought Robert in when I was about 19 years old, and he was living with a woman that they weren't married, but I brought him in to help with royal rangers.

22:13.924 --> 22:18.128
He wasn't a commander, he was a helper, but he was an adult.

22:18.148 --> 22:20.390
We did the background check, we did all that stuff.

22:23.353 --> 22:24.114
And I said, come.

22:24.354 --> 22:29.581
because he found identity and he was learning and he was hearing, because he was doing the Bible studies with us back.

22:29.601 --> 22:33.926
If you remember Royal Rangers back in the old days, we did Bible studies every week.

22:33.946 --> 22:36.710
And he was hearing the Bible studies and he was learning.

22:36.730 --> 22:44.400
And I was helping, having him kind of help lead the Bible study so that he would have to go during the week and actually do a little reading and a little study.

22:44.620 --> 22:48.585
And he was beginning to grow as just a very small seedling.

22:50.708 --> 22:52.530
And then my pastor said, no, you have to kick him out.

22:55.682 --> 22:58.205
because he's living in sin, he's living with a woman, and we can't have that.

22:59.487 --> 23:01.169
Well, okay, pastor, but here's what I don't care.

23:03.111 --> 23:06.035
So I had to ask him to leave, and Robert has never stepped in another church since then.

23:10.600 --> 23:12.703
Because the church wasn't who they needed to be.

23:14.605 --> 23:15.806
Because it's not about us.

23:17.468 --> 23:18.650
It's about them knowing him.

23:20.032 --> 23:22.034
It's not about our personal preferences.

23:22.818 --> 23:28.447
Coming in here on Sunday morning again isn't about what happens up here or even really what I say.

23:30.890 --> 23:41.266
It's about equipping you to go into a lost and dying world and being the hands and feet of Jesus and offering hope and healing to a lost and dying world.

23:47.522 --> 23:54.892
If we were to go just a little bit farther on this drug epidemic, the rates of illicit drug use in our community are higher than the state average.

23:55.413 --> 24:00.479
This tells us that there is a pressing need for the active involvement of the church.

24:00.840 --> 24:08.210
We are called to be salt and light in St. Louis offering support, prayer, and practical help to those who are struggling.

24:08.971 --> 24:13.116
Matthew chapter 5 verse 13 to 16 tells us to be salt and light, right?

24:13.277 --> 24:14.258
You know that passage?

24:14.786 --> 24:15.066
Okay?

24:15.407 --> 24:17.168
Our presence here is no accident.

24:17.409 --> 24:21.713
It is a divine placement for a divine purpose.

24:22.734 --> 24:26.137
You are not in St. Louis by accident, friend.

24:27.038 --> 24:30.702
You didn't find Berea Temple just on a whim.

24:30.762 --> 24:37.288
Whether you looked in the yellow pages, I'm going to date myself, you looked online, or you were referred by somebody.

24:38.409 --> 24:40.031
That was by no accident.

24:41.492 --> 24:43.314
God divinely orchestrated.

24:43.714 --> 24:48.039
your plan and his plan for your purpose and brought you here.

24:48.640 --> 25:04.980
He's placed us here at Berea Temple for what did Esther say, for such a time as this, a time when we can stand as one church and provide a beacon of hope to the lost, the dying, to offer hope to the hopeless and healing to the broken.

25:09.626 --> 25:12.850
When we talk about who we are as a church,

25:18.338 --> 25:19.600
What does our sign say this week?

25:19.620 --> 25:20.261
Did anybody see it?

25:22.343 --> 25:24.867
If you don't know, we have a new insert on the sign.

25:24.927 --> 25:25.788
We talked about that.

25:26.128 --> 25:27.510
And there's a new message out there today.

25:28.171 --> 25:28.952
It's out there this week.

25:29.853 --> 25:30.694
There is hope.

25:34.840 --> 25:36.722
There is hope.

25:38.825 --> 25:39.907
Change can happen.

25:44.753 --> 25:45.554
Do you believe that?

25:46.594 --> 25:48.737
Is there hope for St. Louis?

25:49.959 --> 25:51.842
Is there hope for the lost in the dying?

25:52.843 --> 25:55.287
Is there hope for the drug addicted?

25:56.168 --> 26:00.936
Is there hope for the morally inept?

26:02.478 --> 26:12.533
Is there hope for the LGBT community that is literally one, two, three, four blocks away from us?

26:15.037 --> 26:15.698
Is there hope?

26:17.410 --> 26:18.571
Can we offer it?

26:19.853 --> 26:22.977
Do we have the answer for that?

26:26.040 --> 26:31.107
This is who we are as a church, or it's at least who we need to be.

26:36.813 --> 26:38.756
We need to embrace our calling.

26:40.378 --> 26:42.921
We need to embrace being salt and light.

26:42.981 --> 26:44.703
Matthew, we referenced it earlier.

26:45.083 --> 26:47.186
Matthew chapter five, in verse 13,

26:47.458 --> 26:47.919
There we go.

26:49.443 --> 26:51.428
Says, you are the salt of the earth.

26:51.669 --> 26:54.436
What good is salt if it has lost its flavor?

26:54.496 --> 26:55.719
Can you make it salty again?

26:55.960 --> 26:59.068
It'll be thrown out and trampled underfoot as worthless.

26:59.289 --> 27:03.339
You are the light of the world, a city on a hilltop that cannot be hidden.

27:03.680 --> 27:04.402
No one

27:04.930 --> 27:07.775
No one lights a lamp and then puts it under a basket.

27:07.835 --> 27:12.402
Instead, a lamp is placed on a stand where it gives light to everyone in the house.

27:12.823 --> 27:19.294
In the same way, let your good deeds shine out for all deceit so that everyone will praise your heavenly Father.

27:21.477 --> 27:27.167
We're called to preserve and illuminate the goodness and the truth of God in our city.

27:30.332 --> 27:31.474
So let me ask you a question.

27:32.994 --> 27:36.939
When somebody looks at you out in the community, what do they see?

27:38.341 --> 27:41.585
What light is shined through, shown through?

27:41.605 --> 27:53.841
See our actions, our presence should reflect Christ and bring flavor and light to our community.

27:56.164 --> 28:00.530
Just our presence, the fact that I walked into the room

28:01.474 --> 28:06.602
Because I am with Christ, should change the entire atmosphere.

28:08.465 --> 28:09.566
But do you know somebody?

28:09.686 --> 28:10.748
I know people this way.

28:11.189 --> 28:14.554
They walk into the room and immediately the room just goes, whoa.

28:15.996 --> 28:16.917
There's a heaviness.

28:21.725 --> 28:25.831
And then when they walk out, all of a sudden everything's back to normal.

28:26.472 --> 28:27.714
They used to have a boss like that.

28:28.375 --> 28:30.578
Man, they'd walk in and nobody

28:32.450 --> 28:34.953
always bark and always heavy-handed.

28:37.437 --> 28:44.106
But just our presence, being with Christ, should change the atmosphere of a room.

28:45.067 --> 28:55.602
Second thing that we need to do when we talk about being a community, being and knowing God's heart for our city is we need to understand the importance of praying for our city.

28:56.706 --> 29:03.394
Prayer is a powerful tool that God has given us to enact change and to bring his kingdom here on earth.

29:04.255 --> 29:10.323
Through prayer, we align ourselves with his will and invite his presence into our community.

29:13.266 --> 29:16.070
You ever heard anybody say, well, I'm so sorry.

29:16.851 --> 29:18.312
I can at least pray for you.

29:20.795 --> 29:22.417
That is the best tool we have.

29:23.038 --> 29:24.420
That's not the last tool.

29:24.700 --> 29:26.162
That's not the week.

29:28.418 --> 29:30.040
Man, to say, I'm gonna pray for you.

29:30.720 --> 29:34.264
And don't tell somebody you're gonna pray for them if you don't intend on doing it.

29:36.407 --> 29:44.115
Because when I let, if I tell you I'm gonna pray for you, I'm saying, I'm gonna go put your name before the throne of the Father.

29:45.156 --> 29:48.419
I'm gonna lay your, I'm gonna go, God!

29:48.480 --> 29:53.525
They need you.

29:55.347 --> 29:58.290
It's not that he doesn't know that you already need, that you need him.

30:00.322 --> 30:02.125
But I'm saying, hey, I'm going to jump in with you.

30:03.388 --> 30:05.011
I'm going to become part of that battle.

30:08.558 --> 30:10.401
And I'm going to put your name before the father.

30:10.662 --> 30:17.074
And I'm going to make sure that I've done what I'm called to do and is to lift you up and to encourage

30:18.594 --> 30:22.761
This is what we as a city, as a church need to do for those in our city.

30:22.941 --> 30:28.209
We need to be interceding for our leaders and those that God has placed in authority over us.

30:28.450 --> 30:30.713
It doesn't matter if we agree with them.

30:30.733 --> 30:35.221
I don't care if you're blue or you're red or purple or some other rainbow color.

30:37.484 --> 30:38.626
We're called to pray for them.

30:41.711 --> 30:46.098
First Timothy chapter two, verses one and two says, I urge you, first of all,

30:46.338 --> 30:48.200
Pray for all people.

30:48.621 --> 30:49.862
Ask God to help them.

30:50.182 --> 30:53.726
Intercede on their behalf and give thanks for them.

30:55.028 --> 30:58.151
Yeah, that means give thanks for whichever presidential candidate you don't like.

31:00.954 --> 31:02.836
Or whatever other thing that you don't like.

31:04.839 --> 31:14.930
Pray this way for kings and all who are in authority so that we can live peaceful and quiet lives marked by godliness and dignity.

31:16.834 --> 31:22.039
Pray for them, praying for our city officials, law enforcement, and community leaders.

31:23.941 --> 31:28.525
Seeking God's wisdom and guidance for those in positions of influence.

31:28.545 --> 31:39.115
What you're seeing flipped through the screens right now is every Wednesday night our church has been for a few months already been praying for these areas in our prayer time.

31:40.396 --> 31:43.099
These are just a sample of what we have been praying for.

31:43.159 --> 31:46.642
Not only have we not only have

31:46.722 --> 31:54.412
We've been praying for these areas, but we've been praying for the church, our families, our youth, our children, and so many more things.

31:54.693 --> 32:10.674
The lost of the city, praying for a renewal, for an awakening, praying for repentance, praying for the men and the women of our church, praying for our city, our government leaders, praying for those in our denominational leaders that God has placed over us.

32:12.162 --> 32:17.188
Won't you consider coming and joining us for Wednesday night time of prayer?

32:18.169 --> 32:19.531
Because here's what's happening.

32:21.933 --> 32:24.036
Prayer is what's going to change.

32:25.978 --> 32:29.342
Prayer is what's going to affect change in our church.

32:31.385 --> 32:36.050
Prayer is what's going to make our church be we are.

32:40.738 --> 32:46.006
We need to be praying for our city because we need to be praying for peace and prosperity.

32:46.026 --> 32:51.834
Psalm chapter 122 verse six says, did I miss that one?

32:53.317 --> 32:53.797
There we go.

32:54.919 --> 32:57.082
Says pray for peace in Jerusalem.

32:57.363 --> 33:01.028
May all who love this city prosper.

33:04.213 --> 33:07.698
May we prosper because we love and we're praying for our city.

33:13.762 --> 33:22.816
We need to take this, this passage, and we need to extend it as a call to our city, praying for peace in St. Louis.

33:25.360 --> 33:28.065
I don't care what your political aspirations are.

33:31.029 --> 33:36.658
There is no program that the city's gonna enact that is gonna fix St. Louis.

33:36.938 --> 33:38.040
I'm sorry to tell you that.

33:40.264 --> 33:41.746
There is no easy answer.

33:42.818 --> 33:47.243
what is going to fix our city is the God of our city.

33:49.865 --> 34:01.097
And the way that that's gonna happen is the people of God are going to get on their knees and they're going to cry out to the God of our city to come and to heal their land.

34:01.337 --> 34:06.702
And then he will hear and he will pour out his blessing and he will pour out his spirit.

34:06.722 --> 34:10.226
But it's gonna start on our knees here.

34:17.762 --> 34:22.228
Number three, we talk about God's heart for our city.

34:25.772 --> 34:28.776
God's heart for our city is that we need to engage in the community.

34:31.740 --> 34:35.965
We need to engage in outreach, so engaging community service and outreach.

34:38.648 --> 34:43.555
We need to pray, but we need to put feet.

34:45.197 --> 34:46.258
Rubber meets the road.

34:46.754 --> 34:49.117
Our faith has to translate into action.

34:49.397 --> 34:57.387
By serving our community, we need to demonstrate God's love in practical ways and build bridges that foster hope and healing.

35:02.112 --> 35:02.793
Who do we serve?

35:04.756 --> 35:06.097
Scripture says the least of these.

35:06.698 --> 35:11.304
Matthew 25 verses 35 through 40 says, for I was hungry and you fed me.

35:11.504 --> 35:13.386
I was thirsty and you gave me drink.

35:13.646 --> 35:16.690
I was a stranger and you invited me into your home.

35:16.802 --> 35:18.886
I was naked and you gave me clothing.

35:18.927 --> 35:20.590
I was sick and you cared for me.

35:20.690 --> 35:22.655
I was in prison and you visited me.

35:22.975 --> 35:33.618
Then these righteous ones, who's the righteous ones, the believers in our modern day, it might be y'all, yuns, all y'all, us.

35:37.154 --> 35:48.573
Then these righteous ones will reply, Lord, when did we ever see you hungry and feed you or thirsty and give you something to drink or a stranger and show you hospitality or naked and give you clothing?

35:48.833 --> 35:51.618
When did we ever see you sick or in prison and visit you?

35:53.361 --> 36:01.234
And the king will say, I tell you the truth, when you did it to one of the least of these, my brothers and sisters, you were doing it to me.

36:06.306 --> 36:07.388
This is not in my notes.

36:10.673 --> 36:20.629
But this last week, well, two weeks ago, we came in on a, I don't remember what day it was.

36:23.795 --> 36:26.920
And my son Brandon occasionally will come in here and play the drums.

36:26.960 --> 36:28.763
He gave his set of drums away.

36:28.803 --> 36:30.345
And so he'll just play and practice.

36:30.406 --> 36:33.170
And he goes, Dad,

36:34.498 --> 36:36.220
Somebody here in the church asleep.

36:38.883 --> 36:39.384
Huh?

36:39.404 --> 36:40.945
I thought, okay, somebody's got a key.

36:40.985 --> 36:45.410
They stopped here because it was cool and they just, you know, one of our church folks.

36:46.051 --> 36:47.292
And yeah, I said, who is it?

36:47.693 --> 36:49.795
He goes, I don't know, because I've never seen him before.

36:51.257 --> 36:53.940
And he sat right back there in the back row and was asleep.

36:54.020 --> 36:57.965
And he sent me a picture and I didn't recognize the person, so I came over immediately.

36:58.966 --> 37:02.770
Well, a door was left unlocked that didn't get caught.

37:03.426 --> 37:06.109
And he made his way into the church, and all he was looking for was shelter.

37:09.052 --> 37:09.933
So I started talking to him.

37:09.953 --> 37:10.734
His name was Matthew.

37:13.397 --> 37:18.842
He was some kind of mentally challenged mental health situation.

37:20.544 --> 37:21.605
So of course I didn't call 911.

37:21.705 --> 37:24.628
I called 988.

37:24.669 --> 37:27.692
If you don't know what that is, you need to know what that is.

37:28.913 --> 37:29.874
It's a crisis line.

37:32.130 --> 37:33.713
And I said, hey, listen, I told him.

37:33.733 --> 37:40.947
I said, you know, I don't have any services here for you to sleep or we don't have a pantry or a clothing bank or anything like that.

37:40.967 --> 37:41.729
And I'm so sorry.

37:42.149 --> 37:43.632
But how can we help?

37:43.733 --> 37:45.095
And we tried to figure things out.

37:45.115 --> 37:48.041
And he said, well, I want to go to the hospital, but I don't know where it's at.

37:48.842 --> 37:50.245
And I said, well, here I can show you.

37:50.305 --> 37:54.834
And I gave him instructions on how to go down and just right here to Cardinal Glennon.

38:00.578 --> 38:02.461
And I wish we'd had something more for him.

38:03.643 --> 38:06.247
I wish we were in a position where we had more resources.

38:08.310 --> 38:11.415
It's not to say that we won't someday or won't have eventually.

38:14.199 --> 38:16.002
But who does God call us to serve?

38:17.905 --> 38:20.028
He calls us to serve the least of these.

38:23.653 --> 38:29.362
The homeless, the mentally challenged, the difficult,

38:30.434 --> 38:31.015
the broken.

38:37.261 --> 38:41.666
He calls us to help with the marginalized and the vulnerable of our community.

38:45.530 --> 38:51.116
We need to be able to show Christ's love through tangible acts of kindness and support.

38:51.877 --> 38:56.882
Listen, we can bring a visitor into into Berea Temple and we can sit him down

38:58.050 --> 38:59.251
and we can preach to them.

38:59.732 --> 39:09.124
And yes, the Holy Spirit can do a work on their heart, but most people aren't even open to allowing the Holy Spirit to work on their heart.

39:12.087 --> 39:17.554
Because there's an old saying, it says, people don't care how much you know until they know how much you care.

39:20.698 --> 39:27.506
We cannot simply pay lip service to these areas and say that we're fulfilling the Great Commission and the Great Commandment

39:28.354 --> 39:32.439
We have to put these words into action.

39:35.402 --> 39:36.683
Friends, it doesn't do good.

39:36.744 --> 39:39.527
It's not good enough to just come to church on Sunday.

39:41.529 --> 39:44.953
This is like the minimal.

39:44.973 --> 39:49.498
Do we want to go to heaven just on like the least amount of effort?

39:51.560 --> 39:52.201
Well, okay.

39:52.341 --> 39:53.663
I mean, you accepted Jesus.

39:53.723 --> 39:56.626
Well, that's great, but he's asked us to do

39:57.154 --> 39:59.737
numerous things as being part of the body.

40:04.563 --> 40:14.115
When we talk about engaging the community in service and outreach, how many of us are involved in our community?

40:15.677 --> 40:16.859
How many of us know our neighbors?

40:18.201 --> 40:25.650
How many of us are involved in the neighborhood association, the community organizations, whatever,

40:25.730 --> 40:35.805
things that plug you in to the heartbeat of your neighborhood, of Compton Heights, of where the church is.

40:38.669 --> 40:41.694
See, we need to build strong community relations.

40:41.734 --> 40:47.482
Romans chapter 12 and verse 13 says, when God's people are in need, be ready to help them.

40:47.903 --> 40:50.347
Always be eager to practice hospitality.

40:53.351 --> 40:55.314
Be eager to involve yourself

40:58.498 --> 40:59.279
with the community.

41:06.207 --> 41:09.150
The way to stop violence is to be a friend.

41:11.913 --> 41:23.666
Listen, some of these young boys that are doing some of the horrible things in the city, they're friends with somebody, somebody who doesn't live the life that they're living.

41:25.122 --> 41:32.190
who has an opportunity to speak into their life because they have spent time building a relationship.

41:32.811 --> 41:53.714
They've spent time building a friendship and they're able to speak into the life of the person of these boys, even though they're of a different background or a different mindset, a different political persuasion,

41:54.050 --> 41:55.634
or even religious background.

42:00.406 --> 42:03.314
We have to step outside of our comfort zones.

42:04.998 --> 42:09.650
We have to step outside of our community little clicks.

42:10.722 --> 42:19.511
those things, those people that we've surrounded ourselves with because we've created this little barrier, this little comfort zone that we live in.

42:19.891 --> 42:24.015
And I know that I'm gonna put this person because they're just gonna agree with me.

42:24.676 --> 42:31.102
I'm gonna go talk to them about a situation because I know they're gonna go, oh poor thing.

42:32.263 --> 42:33.124
It's okay.

42:33.885 --> 42:35.126
Let me pray for you.

42:37.688 --> 42:39.410
And I'm gonna surround this person because

42:39.810 --> 42:42.674
They're going to agree with my political persuasion.

42:42.995 --> 42:44.317
Man, I'm mad at so-and-so.

42:46.881 --> 42:48.223
We've got a step beyond those.

42:50.166 --> 43:08.594
We as the church, when we talk about God's heart for the city, it's about his heart for the city, not for the Republicans, not for the Democrats, not for the LGBTQ plus group, not for the blacks, not for the whites, not for the Asians, or the Bosnians, or the Afghanis, or any other people group.

43:11.554 --> 43:14.337
It is his heart for the city because they are his children.

43:14.557 --> 43:15.619
They are his people.

43:17.080 --> 43:27.632
We as a church are called to provide hope and healing in our community.

43:28.032 --> 43:35.280
So as we close, as we kick this series of hope and healing in our community off, I want us to commit ourselves.

43:37.863 --> 43:40.306
We need to understand God's heart

43:40.674 --> 43:41.976
for the city of St. Louis.

43:44.099 --> 43:53.894
We cannot call ourselves Christians, A.G. church members, without putting a practical aspect into our identity.

43:55.276 --> 44:00.824
We cannot call ourselves the body of Christ without what?

44:01.566 --> 44:03.929
Without putting feet to the body?

44:04.650 --> 44:07.154
Without putting hands to the body?

44:09.218 --> 44:23.517
this church, this community, this body of believers at the corner of Compton and Russell cannot stand without the feet that go because God has a heart for St. Louis.

44:23.838 --> 44:29.565
We need to understand as we dive into this series that we are to pray fervently.

44:29.605 --> 44:31.928
It's not just Lord, I pray.

44:31.948 --> 44:33.491
Will you help St. Louis in your name, amen?

44:36.114 --> 44:36.855
Fervently.

44:38.397 --> 44:39.058
God,

44:41.250 --> 44:43.353
pour out your spirit on this city.

44:44.995 --> 44:47.259
God, meet the people who don't know you.

44:49.161 --> 44:58.454
God, we cry out for the people group who have been lied to for generation after generation and have been told that their life isn't good enough.

44:58.474 --> 45:02.260
And so they found identity in somebody else or something else.

45:02.320 --> 45:03.922
God save our city.

45:03.962 --> 45:09.490
Fervently pray.

45:12.418 --> 45:19.971
as if he's coming tomorrow because he just might cry out to God for our city.

45:23.737 --> 45:29.066
And then church, I'm asking you, and be real honest for a moment.

45:30.588 --> 45:31.770
We've had some outreach events.

45:31.790 --> 45:33.233
We had Seek and Save, and that was great.

45:33.473 --> 45:36.338
We had a huge percentage of participation.

45:38.722 --> 45:49.979
And every other event that we've tried to do after that's had a very, very minimal percentage of participation, like two, three, four, five percent of the congregation participate in the event.

45:51.841 --> 46:00.434
Matter of fact, as a follow up, we have VBS that had to be moved due to a scheduling conflict from yesterday to next Saturday.

46:00.735 --> 46:02.617
And you know how many volunteers we have signed up?

46:07.485 --> 46:08.466
This is our children.

46:09.090 --> 46:14.835
This is putting hands and feet to our own kids, much less to those out in the neighborhood.

46:17.278 --> 46:24.284
Besides Pastor Jonathan, Sarah, Pastor Leticia and I and our kids, this is how many signups we've had.

46:26.506 --> 46:28.288
Not being ugly, I'm just telling you a fact.

46:31.852 --> 46:33.953
We have to be the hands and feet of Jesus.

46:36.096 --> 46:38.738
We have to put feet to the fire

46:40.258 --> 46:51.853
and it's gonna take time and we may have to rearrange schedules and we may have to re-prioritize some things that we've allowed to take a higher place than being part of the body in our life and in our families.

46:53.996 --> 46:54.357
Yes.

46:58.362 --> 46:59.223
But it's important.

47:03.549 --> 47:07.154
We need to actively engage in service and outreach to our community.

47:09.297 --> 47:10.258
Because only

47:10.370 --> 47:14.414
then will we fulfill our identity as AG church members.

47:16.977 --> 47:25.066
It's only then that we're going to be able to provide hope and healing to our community as being part of the body of Christ.

47:29.110 --> 47:34.876
So as we close today, as we end our time together, here's what I'm going to ask.

47:34.896 --> 47:36.658
I'm not going to ask you to come forward today.

47:37.858 --> 47:42.163
If you need healing or if you need prayer for salvation, of course, you're always invited to come.

47:44.286 --> 47:45.908
But I'm gonna ask you to stay where you're at.

47:47.190 --> 47:50.053
And I'm gonna ask you to examine your own heart.

47:51.695 --> 47:57.963
Has church been about you and your wants, your desires, your feelings, the way you think things should be?

47:58.003 --> 48:06.994
Do you have God's heart for the city?

48:09.538 --> 48:18.392
Do you have a passion to be A.G. Church members who provide hope and healing to a lost and dying St. Louis?

48:20.555 --> 48:29.209
Are you willing to step out of your comfort zone and put your hands and feet to work?

48:32.033 --> 48:37.522
So as we sing our closing song, I'm just gonna ask you to pray and I'm gonna ask you to reflect and just speak to God.

48:38.882 --> 48:39.623
and to pray.

48:39.703 --> 48:47.271
And when our song is over, I'll come up and we'll close in prayer and we'll dismiss, but I want you to have a time of reflection.

48:47.531 --> 48:55.639
If you need to come down here and you don't need anybody to pray with you, because you're feeling convicted, come to the altar, come to the stairs and pray, you're welcome to do that.

48:56.600 --> 49:00.344
So Father, I pray over each person in this room and within the sound of my voice.

49:03.107 --> 49:06.450
Father, I pray that you would begin to speak to hearts.

49:07.234 --> 49:10.819
call people, separate them out.

49:10.839 --> 49:13.203
Place a burden on their heart for the city.

49:13.503 --> 49:18.330
Place a burden on their heart for specific areas and specific people.

49:18.651 --> 49:23.178
There are some that heard the numbers for the drug addicted and their hearts were quickened.

49:23.398 --> 49:30.689
There were some that heard the numbers about the health decline of the mental health folks and their hearts were quickened.

49:32.111 --> 49:36.978
God, I pray that you would foster that within their heart, Lord.

49:38.114 --> 49:56.130
grow it and put feet to it and hands to it so that we as the church will rise up and be the hands and feet of Jesus to our city.

49:56.150 --> 49:57.934
We ask these things in the name of Jesus.

49:58.755 --> 50:00.178
Amen.

